Title: FOUNT: BLOCKBUSTERS IN TERMINAL
Credit: Written by
Author: Beetle and Bee
Source: Based on Fount v0.9.7
Draft date: May 14, 2026
Contact: beetle@zenstudio.io
Notes: This tutorial is an interactive screenplay. Read it to master Fount's professional production tools.

# ACT I: THE ZEN STUDIO

INT. THE APARTMENT - NIGHT

= Beetle and Bee sit in the soft glow of a terminal. The cursor blinks like a steady pulse.

BEETLE
Welcome home.

BEE
(looking at the screen)
It's different. cleaner. The dashboard... I just tapped `Tab` and `Enter` to get here from the start screen.

BEETLE
That's the new Home Dashboard. Threaded, simple, and fast.

Beetle types a command. The text around the cursor stays bright, while everything else dims into a soft grey.

BEETLE (CONT'D)
`/set highlight`. It's called **Active Block Focus**. It keeps your mind on the paragraph you're actually writing.

BEE
It feels like... the world just fell away.

# ACT II: THE ARCHITECT'S SKELETON

INT. THE APARTMENT - LATER

= They begin to map out the structure of their story using professional templates.

BEETLE
We aren't just writing lines anymore. We're building a structure.

Beetle types `/structure`. A picker appears. He selects "Michael Hauge's 6 Stage Journey".

BEE
Wait, the script just... populated itself?

BEETLE
Exactly. It imported the beats. You see those `#` symbols? Those are **Sections**. They build the navigator on the left (`Ctrl+T`). And those `=` lines? **Synopses**. They fill the **Index Cards** (`/ic`).

BEE
(pointing to a line)
And these double brackets? `[[props: A silver locket]]`.

BEETLE
**Production Tags**. Departmental metadata. VFX, SFX, Wardrobe, Props. We're tracking the physical world while we imagine the emotional one.

# ACT III: THE REVISION MARKS

INT. THE APARTMENT - DEEP NIGHT

= The intensity of writing increases. Beetle toggles a new mode.

BEETLE
We're in the second draft now. `/revision on`.

Beetle edits a line of dialogue. A bright yellow `*` appears in the right margin.

BEE
What's that star?

BEETLE
A **Revision Mark**. Every line we touch while Revision Mode is active gets flagged. It tells the director and the cast exactly what changed since the last print.

BEE
And when we're happy with it?

BEETLE
`/revision bake`. The marks disappear, the changes are locked, and we move forward.

# ACT IV: THE X-RAY AUDIT

INT. THE APARTMENT - DAWN

= Using X-Ray Mode to analyze the production breakdown.

Beetle types `/xray` and hits `4`.

BEETLE
Tab 4. The **Production Breakdown**. 

BEE
It's a list of everything we need! Every prop, every wardrobe change... it's all indexed from those tags we wrote.

BEETLE
Fount doesn't just read your story; it understands your production. Pacing (`Tab 2`), Word Counts (`Tab 1`), and now, the Physical Reality of the set.

BEE
(smiling)
It's time to export.

BEETLE
Press `Ctrl+E`. Choose PDF. Your revision marks, your scene numbers, and your bold headings... they're all there.

BEE
Let's send it to the world.

> FADE OUT.

[End of Tutorial. Use `/home` to go back to the dashboard. Happy writing!]
